body:
This is a diagnostic enhancement request in two similar parts.
Currently (1.58.0-nightly ff0e14829 2021-10-31) this gives no errors nor warnings:

```rust
#![allow(dead_code, unused_variables)]
fn main() {
    let x = 1_u32;
    let y = x as u64;
    const X: u32 = 1;
    const Y: u64 = X as _;
}
```

But I'd like a help message that suggests to replace the "as" with a from, nudging the programmer to write:

```rust
#![allow(dead_code, unused_variables)]
fn main() {
    let x = 1_u32;
    let y = u64::from(x);
    const X: u32 = 1;
    const Y: u64 = X as _;
}
```

And eventually once the two features are stable, nudging to write:

```rust
#![feature(const_num_from_num, const_trait_impl)]
#![allow(dead_code, unused_variables)]
fn main() {
    let x = 1_u32;
    let y = u64::from(x);
    const X: u32 = 1;
    const Y: u64 = u64::from(X);
}
```
